  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">My Home, Our Common Home - Ecological Conversion and Peace Culture</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will strengthen the capacities of young people, teachers, parents and caregivers and five schools in two municipalities of the Magdalena Medio region, in order to promote and foster a culture of peace, gender equality, coexistence and solidarity in harmony with the environment. Students, parents, and carers will increase their knowledge and design practical tools oriented to the care of the environment and the resolution of conflicts in a peaceful way. There will be engagement with five schools and institutions, supporting headteachers and teachers to strengthen their institutional strategies and promote spaces oriented to the design and implementation of actions in rural education with emphasis on the development of social-emotional competencies and care for the environment.</narrative>
  </description>
